</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2 id="8-running-the-system-locally">8. Running the System Locally</h2>
<pre><code class="language-bash"># 1. Install dependencies
npm install

# 2. Configure .env.local (see Section 6)

# 3. Run Supabase schema (via Supabase SQL Editor)
# Open supabase/schema.sql and execute in Supabase dashboard

# 4. Start development server
npm run dev

# 5. Open in browser
# http://localhost:3000
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h2 id="9-user-manual-summary">9. User Manual Summary</h2>
<h3 id="for-educators">For Educators</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Register</strong> at <code>/register</code> → select "Educator"</li>
<li><strong>Login</strong> at <code>/login</code></li>
<li><strong>Create Quiz</strong>: Dashboard → "+ New Quiz" → fill details → add questions → Save</li>
<li><strong>Publish</strong>: Click "Publish" on any saved quiz</li>
<li><strong>View Results</strong>: Click "Results" on a published quiz</li>
<li><strong>Analytics</strong>: Dashboard sidebar → "Grade Reports"</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="for-students">For Students</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Register</strong> at <code>/register</code> → select "Student"</li>
<li><strong>Login</strong> at <code>/login</code></li>
<li><strong>Take a Quiz</strong>: Dashboard → click any quiz → "Take Quiz →"</li>
<li><strong>Answer Questions</strong>: Select options or type responses</li>
<li><strong>Submit</strong>: Click "Submit Quiz" or let timer auto-submit</li>
<li><strong>View Results</strong>: After submission → results page with AI feedback</li>
<li><strong>History</strong>: Dashboard → "My Results"</li>
</ol>
    </body>
